# Video 1

Open claude code in vs code project folder 
Run this comment to launch claude — claud
We can run bash commands in claude code just press shift + 1 then run commands
Basically it's recommended to use bash commands in claude code rather than opening a new terminal so claude can remember those commands in his history 
It is a best practice to use git and GitHub while building projects
We mostly work on running projects and rarely on scratch one's 

Ask claude basics questions about the project like — 
1. what this project do? 
2. What tech stack used?
3. Explain the project structure 

/init - to initiate the project 
/exit - to end the session 


# Video 2

Use claude code with ollama — 
ollama launch claude 
Choose the model — use kwen 3.5 (best for coding)
local models are in [others] and cloud models are on top — ollama launch claude
I downloaded qwen2.5:3b using this command ollama pull qwen2.5:3b in my system

